		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="pacific oysters" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-triploid-oyster-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Watch out oysters: climate change is coming for you. Photo by Picture Partners/Alamy Stock Photo</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">So Long Triploids, Hello Creamy Oysters</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Triploid oysters—selectively bred for summer eating—suffer in high temperatures. Is their plight enough to get us to change our oyster eating habits?</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/devon-fredericksen/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Devon Fredericksen</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						May 22, 2024 | 1,000 words, about 5 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
